This paper deals with the analysis of cellular network traces, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the effectiveness of existing strategies to improve network capacity, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The generation of synthetic deployment and demand profiles involves statistical modeling and data analysis, which could be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper mentions the load served by LTE networks, which could be related to cs.MM (Multimedia).
